Isn't it icon only button? Remove the aria-label attribute for buttons with text (including icon only buttons in table row actions and password toggle button)

That is correct. The aria-label is not needed since we have added the text to the button on line 12. We need the title attribute for mouse users that hover the icon.
Done.
remove aria labels
Same here. Remove the aria-label attribute for buttons with text.
Yes, we do not need aria-labels when there is button text like on line 10.
Done
remove aria labels
Same here. Remove the aria-label attribute for buttons with text.

Yes, the aria-label means some screen readers will read the same text multiple times. That is why we are adding the text to buttons using the sr-only class and removing aria-labels. Most screen readers will not read both the title and the button text. The title attribute is beneficial to mouse users as most browsers show the title value on mouse hover.

This is a good start, but:

1. What happens when there is an icon and we need to be able to have the title when the user mouses over the icon?
2. Do we need to make the btn-icon-only class dynamic?

1. It makes sense. Should we modify this component in the same commit?
2. We can make it, but it won't affect until there is an icon in the button.

Yes...make the changes in this commit. Most of the buttons in tables are icon only with the exception of client sessions.You mentioned in scrum that you made the changes in this commit, but I am not seeing any updates following the comments.
Done. I made provision to add title for icon only button and added class dynamically. I was looking for better solution that is the reason i didn't push the code.
This is the export button. Should this also be updated to remove the aria-label?
Done. I wasn't sure since it is link not button.
Did you check the rendered markup in the browser? Do we need a <span> element with sr-only class?
Done. Removed aria-label. And not sure if we need sr-only class to the link element.
We do need the screen reader only text. That is what replaces the aria-label and is the update we have made in all of the files.
Done. Added the screen reader only text.

Only needed when not btnIconOnly. When an icon is not used, as is the case with client sessions, the title that is in the icon slot is fallback text and will render on the screen to the user. In this implementation, the rendered output is now one visible and one screen reader only of the same text, so it will read twice to the screen reader.
https://v3.vuejs.org/guide/component-slots.html#fallback-content This is the rendered output
Done. Got it.
Did you look at what was rendered out for this change? I am still seeing both the value being injected from the empty slot and the <span> element.
Done. Not sure why this file wasn't pushed up with last commit.
It was pushed up...the issue is that the value is incorrect?
Done. Thanks.
